      "id": "PopularPost320333",
      "post_content": "I think people are severely undervaluing this card in r/g suspend. Dropping a hasty 5/5 on people 2 turns earlier than anticipated can put people in a very bad spot; obviously remove the last two counters with this, otherwise the element of surprise is lost. You can even pop creatures into play from suspend during combat.   \n  \n...and that's only ONE mode, the pump/trample is nice for the beefy creatures that r/g attracts, particularly because most of them lack native trample. Being able to mainboard artifact removal is also nice, since you pretty much lose something like [Sword of Fire and Ice](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sword of Fire and Ice) if it lands and you aren't prepared to destroy it.",
      "posted_by": "auriscope",
